Jose Mourinho was in good spirits ahead of Tottenham‘s game against Leicester and even poked fun at Kolo Toure’s weight. Mourinho greeted Toure, who is now working as assistant manager to Brendan Rodgers, as he arrived pitchside at the Tottenham Hotspur Stadium. After a customary fist-bump, the Spurs boss tapped the Ivorian’s stomach and seemed to suggest that he had put on a bit of weight. Watch the video here. The post Watch: Jose Mourinho cheekily mocks Kolo Toure’s weight appeared first on Football365. Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world. Brendan Rodgers says he has no thoughts about leaving Leicester following reports that Tottenham made tentative inquiries before replacing sacked manager Mauricio Pochettino with Jose Mourinho. The post Rodgers 'very happy' at Leicester following Spurs link appeared first on The Guardian Nigeria News - Nigeria and World News. Source: Guardian November 21, 2019 In "News" Tottenham boss Jose Mourinho has spoken out over Serge Aurier’s decision to line out versus Newcastle, despite the tragic recent death of his brother. Son on target Spurs are currently locked in Premier League action with the Magpies at St. James’ Park. Mourinho’s men headed into proceedings with their tails… July 15, 2020 In "Sports" Piatek linked with Tottenham Tottenham lost one of their key players at the beginning of this year when Harry Kane limped off vs Southampton. Spurs would then confirm that Kane is expected to be out until April. @HKane injury update. #THFC #COYS — Tottenham Hotspur (@SpursOfficial) January 9, 2020 https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js… January 11, 2020 In "Sports"